  "caveats": [
    "Reference-state redundancy: only 20 unique (qpos,qvel) states among the 110 saved states inherited from the action-validity probe; 91/110 are bit-identical copies of one resting pose (the ant settles into a static equilibrium and the source episode saved it repeatedly). All 110 states share a single goal.",
    "Consequence: bootstrap CIs in per_set are overconfident (they treat 91 replications of one state as independent); regime splits standing_moving/standing_stationary/fast_spin are polluted by median-splits over 91 numerical-zero speeds; heading strata are degenerate (one pose dominates).",
    "Verdict robustness: recomputed on the 20 unique states and on the 16 moving states (|v_xy|>0.05) the conclusion is unchanged -- see state_coverage_audit; local sigma<=0.2 spread stays 10-50x below the meaningful threshold while uniform actions exceed it.",
    "The same redundancy affects the earlier forensic-audit and local-ranking probes, which used the same saved-state file (35 states there ~= mostly the one resting pose)."
  ]
